summary: I see everyone complaining about Scorbunny possibly being Fire/Fighting in the final evolution, and I get why I also see...
body:
I see everyone complaining about Scorbunny possibly being Fire/Fighting in the final evolution, and I get why

I also see everyone thinking of unique final evolution types, and I get why

But what about just staying pure Fire in each stage? We haven’t seen that since Typhlosion. In 1999. Almost 20 years ago.

blog.name: too-cool-for-facebook
blog.title: Too Cool for Facebook
blog.description:
All that fun stuff that's too cool for Facebook but not quite artsy enough to put on deviantArt. Elliot Morgan put it best when he said, "Facebook has just become a big family reunion, except without all the good food." I ran away from MySpace because people I knew IRL were there. And now I've run away from FB for the same reason - mostly bc I'm tired of listening to my dumbass redneck relatives talk about shit they have no knowledge of. Also, INFJ. Writing it here bc I can never effing remember.
New to my blog? Then you probably need to check out this post: http://too-cool-for-facebook.tumblr.com/post/109313455847/i-have-gotten-like-a-shit-ton-of-followers-over

title: Pokemon Trainers
body:
Ranked by a casual Pokemon fan who enjoys the Anime but doesn’t play the game.

Red

What can I say, nothing beats a classic. 8/10

Kris

Who is this girl? I’ve never seen her in my life. But I kinda want to. 8/10

Ethan

6/10. If Red is Coca-cola, then Ethan is Diet Coke.

May

I know you! You were in the cartoon! For the first time, the show actually treated a second trainer like a co-protagonist! 9/10, you shoulda had more screentime.

Brendan

Ooh, another mystery trainer I don’t know about. I’m getting Quicksilver vibes off of him. 8/10

Leaf

Design’s pretty cute, but the way her hand is posed reminds me too much of Butch Hartman. 7/10

Lucas and Dawn

These two are fashionistas. Their outfits balance hip and rediculous. 9/10

Hilbert

Diet Caffeine Free Coca-cola. 4/10

Lyra

It’s a me! Mario! 7/10, shoulda included a Mario hat.

Nate and Hilda

Look at that hair! It’s so messy! I love it. Also, kudos to Hilda for pulling off a look that I’d more associate with the male trainers of the series. 9/10

Calem and Rosa

A swore a ghost just passed behind me and whispered the word “Hipster” into my ears. 7/10

Elio and Selene

Are these gremlins? 8/10

Serena

This chick looks like and has the name of the popular chick in High School. I don’t really care for it. 4/10

Chase

This is like the type of coke you find in the tiny cans. This is Red Junior. 9/10

Elaine

According to Bulbapedia, Eevee is 14 pounds. This chick is just casually carrying that weight on her head. 8/10

Candela

Strong. Probably makes for a good leader. 8/10

Blanche

Mysterious and Icy and stern. She looks like I’d piss her off easily. 6/10

Spark

A beautiful fuck-up boy. I love him. 9/10

Ash


Another beautiful fuck-up boy and also a classic. Maybe a tad bit overused, but it’s not like I can find myself hating him. 8/10

Misty

If the Pokemon Anime needs a new protagonist, I say we let Misty take on the lead role. I know, I know, she wasn’t a player character in the original game… but honestly she’s so under utilized. 10/10, exactly the type of trainer we need in the lead role/

Brock

Oh hey, this is the guy everybody said I looked like when I was still in School. 7/10

Samus in Super Smash Bros. Brawl

No, she’s not an official trainer. But she rescued the Smash version of Pikachu, fights alongside him in battle, and defeats Tabuu with Pikachu at her side. I’m assuming that after the series Samus just straight up adopts him. 9/10.

summary: 👀 Favorite place in the world? (I'm the anon from the previous question, sorry I forgot about rule 1)
question: 👀 Favorite place in the world? (I'm the anon from the previous question, sorry I forgot about rule 1)
answer:
Now, this was a question that Yveltal really had to take some time and think about. His favorite place? He wasn't really known to travel much, he had only been outside the actual region of Kalos a handful of times. 

He nodded to himself, having decided on his answer.

‘‘Kalos, in general, is quite a charming place, but if the answer you seek is a more specific one.. I’d have to say my own little cave.’’ ‘‘It’s peaceful around these parts, not many beings dare disturb death as it slumbers.’’

( No worries! I did just add the rules page a moment ago, so I can’t expect everyone to have seen it already. But I wouldn’t feel good answering an ask of that nature when I’ve stated in the rules that I wouldn’t, even if it happened to be sent before the rules were actually noticed. )
